The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 ICC anti-doping policy

Any player found guilty of a doping practice could be subject to the following sanctions: 

a) Suspension for two years in the case of a first violation or a lifetime ban for a second offence 

b) A fine, loss of financial assistance, rewards or records received during the tournament 




